
[1]twit

   TWIT, v.t. [L. ad, to.] To reproach; to upbraid; as for some previous
   act. He twitted his friend of falsehood.

   With this these scoffers twitted the christians.

   Aesop minds men of their errors, without twitting them for what is
   amiss.
